      "text": "**Find**\nSelect any text and ⌘-F to see only the sentences in the document which contain the selected text. You can click on the text in the results to open the document at that section or ⌘-F again to exit or ESC. The text you selected will of course appear in the Find results and is marked by the fact that the line holding the find term is not bolded.\nView\n• n to see only Names and headings\n• g to see any Glossary terms and headings\n• z to zoom the document 1 step\n• Select text and h (or ⌘-control-h) to Highlight\n• h to see any text you have Highlighted, as well as all headings\n• Select text and x to strike a red line through the text\n"
